  "prompt": "Is power steering fluid the same as brake fluid?",
  "response": "No, power steering fluid is not the same as brake fluid. These fluids serve different purposes and have different properties:\n\n1. **Power Steering Fluid**:\n   - Purpose: It is used in the power steering system to help with the lubrication and smooth operation of the steering mechanism.\n   - Properties: It is typically hydraulic fluid, which can be made of mineral oil or synthetic oil.\n   - Function: It transmits the pressure needed for power steering and lubrication of components within the steering system.\n\n2. **Brake Fluid**:\n   - Purpose: It is used in the braking system to provide the necessary pressure for braking force and to ensure proper functioning of the brake components.\n   - Properties: It is typically glycol-based or silicone-based fluid.\n   - Function: It transfers the force from the brake pedal to the brake mechanism to enable braking.\n\nUsing the wrong type of fluid in either system can lead to damage and potentially dangerous malfunctions. Always use the manufacturer's recommended fluids for your vehicle's power steering and braking systems.",
